@*
    Small-business service page. This is a SHELL, not a live pitch. Per the spec's plan-vs-done
    rule: Scott has no small-business build to point at yet, so this page has the same structure
    as the nopCommerce one but NO proof section and deliberately soft claims. It goes live for
    real once the roofer site ships and there's something true to say. Copy is placeholder.

    Do NOT write present-tense claims here that imply an established small-business practice.
*@

<section class="section--lede">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="topper">Small business websites</p>
        <h1 class="header">A website built to be found</h1>
        <p class="text lede__text">
            A fast, clean site for your business that search engines can actually read. Built
            on the Colorado Front Range, for local businesses.
        </p>
        <a class="button button--lg" asp-controller="Contact" asp-action="Index">Schedule a consultation</a>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section--alt">
    <div class="container">
        <p class="topper">What you get</p>
        <h2 class="title">The essentials, done well</h2>

        <ul class="features">
            <li class="feature">
                <h3 class="feature__title">Fast</h3>
                <p class="feature__text">
                    Built to load quickly on a phone, which is where most of your customers
                    will find you.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li class="feature">
                <h3 class="feature__title">Findable</h3>
                <p class="feature__text">
                    Real pages search engines can read on the first pass, so you show up when
                    someone searches for what you do.
                </p>
            </li>
            <li class="feature">
                <h3 class="feature__title">Yours</h3>
                <p class="feature__text">
                    A site built around your business, not squeezed into a generic template.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</section>

@*
    No proof section yet, on purpose. When the roofer site is live, a proof block goes here
    linking to it, matching the nopCommerce page.
*@

<partial name="_CallToAction" model="@("Thinking about a new site?")" />
